<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pike1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pike,</orth> a sort of lance: <bibl n="shak. ven 620" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 620</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.244" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 244</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.152" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 6, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.399" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 399</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 39</bibl>. <cit><quote>you must put in the --s with a vice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 2, 21</bibl></cit>, i. e. central spikes sometimes used in targets, to which they were affixed by means of a screw.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>